#Title#
Replay Center | NBA Official
#Content#
Skip to content Toggle navigation NBA Official Home Replay Center Replay Archive 2015-16 Updates Triggers About Video Rulebook Today’s Officials Twitter Search for:   Beginning with the 2014-15 NBA regular season, the NBA will launch its new state-of-the-art NBA Replay Center, based in Secaucus, N.J.  The NBA Replay Center will be fueled by a groundbreaking high-speed arena network to enhance the performance of NBA referees and to accelerate the replay review process. 94 The Replay Center is equipped with 94 HD monitors 30 The bandwidth capacity of the new network could download the entire digitized Library of Congress – more than 158 million documents – in just over 30 minutes. 29 All 29 NBA arenas are connected directly to the NBA Replay Center in Secaucus, NJ. 20 The NBA Replay Center features 20 work stations, including 17 Replay Operator stations and 3 Replay Manager stations. 15 NBA Referees consult with the NBA Replay Center based on 15 instant replay triggers. Copyright NBA Media Ventures, LLC | NBA Media Ventures, LLC. All rights reserved. No portion of this site may be duplicated, redistributed, or manipulated in any form. By accessing any information on this site, you agree to abide by the NBA.com Network Policy and Terms of Use
